# Coding-Agents Telemetry Convention

This is the **strict** contract between every coding-agent vendor and OpenLit. Every adapter, every native-telemetry mapping, every query has to match it exactly. Drift in either direction (renaming an attribute, switching units, adding ad-hoc vendor-namespaced keys) breaks the `/coding-agents` and `/agents` views in subtle, hard-to-diagnose ways. When in doubt, prefer this document over what any individual vendor's docs claim.

The companion authoring rule is `coding-agents-hook.mdc` (failure modes + checklist). This rule is the **schema**.

---

## 1. Canonical schema (single source of truth)

Everything OpenLit reads or rolls up speaks one of two namespaces:

- **`coding_agent.*`** — OpenLit-owned, defined in `sdk/go/semconv/coding_agent.go` (Go) and `cli/gen/semconv.ts` (TS mirror). Specific to coding agents — no other product surface uses these.
- **`gen_ai.*`** — OpenTelemetry GenAI semantic conventions (with a few OpenLit-stamped additions in `sdk/go/semconv/genai.go`). Shared with the SDK / LLM observability surface.

**Hard rules:**

1. Adapters MUST stamp `coding_agent.session.id` on every span. No exceptions.
2. Adapters MUST stamp `coding_agent.client` (vendor identifier) on every span. Allowed values: `cursor`, `claude-code`, `codex`, `windsurf`. Add new values to `sdk/go/semconv/coding_agent.go` AND `src/client/src/types/agents.ts` AND re-run `go generate`.
3. `gen_ai.system` MUST be the LLM provider, not the agent vendor: `anthropic`, `openai`, `google`, `xai`, `mistral`. Use the `inferProvider(model, vendor)` helper.
4. Numeric attributes are emitted as numbers, NEVER as strings. Tokens are `int64`. Cost is `float64` in USD. Duration is `int64` in milliseconds.
5. Timestamps are RFC3339-with-nanos when stamped as strings, or the OTel span's intrinsic start/end when stamped as span time. NEVER unix seconds, never milliseconds-since-epoch.
6. Enums (capture mode, outcome, edit decision, classification) MUST be exactly one of the defined values. Use the `semconv.CodingAgent*` constants — never inline a literal.

