The eight `coding_agent.session.{lines,edit,commit,pr}*` rollup
attributes are an additive fast path — they let the per-session
`listSessions` query render code-impact without scanning every
`coding_agent.edit.decision` / `coding_agent.git.*` child span.
For sessions where the rollup is missing (Codex never emits a
`SessionEnd`; in-flight CC / Cursor sessions also lack the rollup),
the query layer falls back to per-event aggregation with the
`greatest(rollup, sum)` pattern documented in `queries.ts`.

